omponent for the reintegration of the offender. Drawing on his experience as a judge, prosecutor, and public defender, London offers a pragmatic vision of restorative justice that integrates its core values with real-world applications for even the most serious violent crimes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aConfidence. 0aCrime. 0aPunishment. 0aRestorative justice. 0aTrust. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978193504967840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781935049678423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781935049678/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK